    Wonderful Mall With Great Restaurants
    My husband and I visited Portugal for our 40th anniversary and went to this huge indoor shopping mall several times while in Lisbon. First, we wanted to tour the mall to see how the locals enjoy their shopping. Then we noticed there were so many places to eat (downstairs and up top) -- with the mall so close to our B & B, that we ended up eating dinner there many nights at different places. Even the food court had amazing places and food (not as casual as in the US malls), and some of the top floor restaurants had delicious foods with great outdoor views! It was wonderful!
    Visited September 2023
    Traveled as a couple

Racist Supermarket Staff
Apr 2024 • Solo
Mamadu Cande arbitrarily let one customer go in front of another at the supermarket checkout line.

I was the next customer at the checkout, I am an Asian woman with 11 items. Mamadu Cande asked me if I would be okay with letting a customer behind me, a White woman in her 30s with 1 item, checkout first.

I said "No. Why?!", incredulous. Mamadu Cande grabbed her item from behind mine on the checkout belt, scanned and allowed her to pay first anyway.

It was against my will, illogical, unjustified, unexplained, inexplicable, probably racist and definitely arbitrary.

I complained. Mamadu Cande simply smiled like I was being ridiculous, and gave no explanation. What is the point of queuing if the checkout staff gets to pick and choose who gets to go first? If all customers behind me have only one item, do I ever get to pay and leave?

The other customer was able-bodied and young, did not appear to be in a rush, and did not request to go first. We were not in a 10 item or less checkout line. There was completely no reason for Mamadu Cande to do what he did. I cannot believe this happened at all, and in El Corte Ingles, allegedly the best high end supermarket in Portugal.
Written April 12, 2024

Melanie T
New York City, NY7,021 contributions
The food court is not it
Dec 2023 • Couples
When I went to Spain a few years ago, I had visited El Corte Ingles and loved it. So when I found out they had a location in Lisbon, I definitely wanted to check it out. Unfortunately, this one just wasn't it. Maybe my expectations were set to high because of the Barcelona one (since it is a Spanish store after all), but the Lisbon one was just lacking. The food court was just filled with over-priced restaurants. The Cafeteria was reasonably priced, but none of the menu items appealed to us. There wasn't any Portugues menu items - it was just basic sandwiches, salads, and burgers. Visting the food court was our main reason for coming here so unless you are planning to actually shop here, I'd recommend skipping it.
Written February 12, 2024

Large Upscale Department Store & Grocery with Restaurants
Nov 2023 • Couples
Large, modern upscale department store in the Saldanha district of Lisbon. The Sao Sebastiao Metro station stop takes you directly into the complex without having to step outside. Besides selling the usual items found in a department store, El Corte Ingles also has numerous restaurants, a food court, a pharmacy, a florist, and large grocery store. If you’re in the vicinity, El Corte Ingles is worth a visit and be sure to try and catch a bite to eat in one of the numerous eateries and restaurants.
